<section class="intro">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row text-center">
      <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
        <%= image_tag('lightning.svg', class: "img-responsive") %>
        <h1>Active Record CUD</h1>
      </div>
    </div> <!-- /row -->
  </div> <!-- /container -->
</section> <!-- /intro -->
<section class="content">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
        <h2><a href="https://github.com/binnacle-io/binnacle_ar" target="blank">Active Record CUD</a> (Create-Update-Delete) interceptor for Binnacle</h2>
        <p>Adds ActiveRecord callbacks for create, update and delete that will signal Binnacle with the state of the object (to_json). Use in conjunction with the <a href="https://github.com/binnacle-io/binnacle-js" target="blank">binnacle-js library</a> create a rich near-realtime experience for your users.</p>
        <p>To enabled signals from an ActiveRecord model simply use the the <strong>binnacle_signal_on</strong> class method:</p>
        <figure class="highlight">
<pre><code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby">class Article < ActiveRecord::Base
  binnacle_signal on: [:create, :update, :destroy]
end</code></pre>
        </figure>
        <p>To view the Coffeescript client-side implementation of this demo see the source file <a href="https://github.com/binnacle-io/binnacle-rails-showcase/blob/master/app/assets/javascripts/articles.coffee.erb" target="blank">articles.coffee.erb</a></p>
        <%= render 'articles/articles' %>
      </div>
    </div> <!-- /row -->
  </div> <!-- /container -->
</section> <!-- /content -->
